  * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *

  Purpose :    TSO command to LOCK terminal (restricted to only
  ---------    authorized users : SYSTEM group).

               Function : terminal is locked until the correct two
                          secret keywords are typed in, or, the SESSION
                          is terminated when the elapsed maximum WAIT
                          time (2 hours) has expired (it is decremented
                          continuously in REAL time from the moment the
                          LOCK command is invoked, even if somebody
                          push (unlock failure) the ENTER key.

               Mandatory : if you are an authorized user, you must
                          contact the SYSTEM group manager, to define
                          your two secret keywords, unless you cannot
                          use this command.

  Syntax :     LOCK
